              .site-content.margin-bottom-small
                h3 Size System
                p Here's where the mixin and the media queries are put to work. For my type system, I wanted to simplify how I handle font sizes across screen sizes. It's not perfect and you can add more media queries to handle specific sizes. I wanted to cover the main type sizes you usually see in Photoshop or Figma.

                p To use this system, just add @extend .t-xx; to your line of code. The downside to this that you cannot use @extend inside a media query. So this will keep you constrained to simple font sizes for your elements, which is a good thing in the long run.
