        #global.site-content
          .row
            .col-12
              .site-content.margin-bottom-small
                h3 Global
                p The settings within the HTML and BODY tags set the precident for the rest of the type settings. The font-size of 62.5% in the HTML tag helps tell the browser to use "font-size:10px", but using percentages. This allows people who have vision impairments to bump the font size up. Then you do another reset at the body level, which for me, I use 18px font sizes.
